<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gines Takes Tour of Asturia Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Manuel Fernandez Gines of Spain
riding for Banesto won the Tour of Asturia cycling following
Sunday's sixth and last stage over 162 kilometers from Cangas de
Narcea and Oviedo.
</P>
<P>
He edged out Dutchman Jeroen Blijlevens in a sprint finish.
</P>
<P>
Cassio Freitas of Brazil broke away in the early stages and he
held the lead for some 100 kilometres, before riders from Banesto
and Toscaf, the latter seeking to help Russian Sergei Smetanin,
moved to rein him in.
</P>
<P>
Blijlevens eventually moved unsuccessfully to oust Gines as his
TVM teammates set him up for a furious finale. 
</P>
</TEXT>
