<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cipollini Retains Giro Leader's Jersey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Mario Cipollini snatched his
second Giro d'Italia stage win in 24 hours as one of his chief
rivals crashed on the final bend on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 30-year-old Cipollini strengthened his grip on the lead as
compatriot Nicola Minali crashed 200 meters from the finish of the
211-km second leg from Mestre to Cervia.
</P>
<P>
Minali's back wheel skidded sideways as he chased Cipollini out
of the final bend and Minali and Elio Aggiano slid into the
spectator barriers.
</P>
<P>
Czech Jan Svorada pipped Endrio Leoni for second place with
Cipollini comfortably clear at the line after a final lap
averaging more than 50 kph.
</P>
<P>
Fabio Baldato, another Cipollini rival, had to fight back from
an earlier crash on the 7.8-km circuit and was critical of the
organisation for planning a course with so many corners.
</P>
<P>
Cipollini, who's built a career out of capturing such stages,
also took Saturday's opening leg in a closing dash, edging
countryman Minali.  
</P>
</TEXT>
