<HEADLINE> STDS: Main Cause of Infertility of Africans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Sexually Transmitted Diseases
(STDS) have been blamed for being the main cause of infertility
among African men.
</P>
<P>
The Invitro Fertilisation (IVF) Association of Zimbabwe today
said infertility in this southern African nation of 11.5 million
was a 30 to 40 percent male problem.
</P>
<P>
And in females, the association said infertility resulted from
blocked tubes as a result of tubal pregnancy, disease and other
interruptions.
</P>
<P>
About 10 to 15 percent of males in the western world were
unable to conceive and the number is more in Africa because of
the prevalence of STDS.
</P>
<P>
The association, formed in 1987, aimed to provide counsel and
advice for patients, to liaise between its medical team and
members and to undertake any other activities that might further
the cause of IVF. 
</P>
</TEXT>
