<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-18 17:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Strikes Oil, Gas Deal with French Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Iran announced here today that it
has signed a 3-billion-U.S. dollar contract with French Total
Company for oil and gas exploitation in southern Iran.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Ali Akbar Velayati said at a press conference
that the agreement was signed by Iran's oil ministry and the
French Total Company.
</P>
<P>
Velayati said that the project will be launched in South Pars,
a new and major oil and gas center in south Iran. The Total will
be involved in digging and transferring oil and gas to the
international market.
</P>
<P>
Observers here noted that the latest deal might spark a trade
row between the United States and France because U.S. President
Bill Clinton signed a bill to punish foreign companies which
invest more than 40 million dollars in Iran's oil and gas sector.
</P>
<P>
Iran, which has made some progress in thwarting the
U.S. sanction in oil and gas sector, also signed a
140-million-dollar contract with a UK-Canadian consortium --
Britain's Pell Frischmann and Canada's Bow Valley.
</P>
<P>
The Total company signed a 600-million-dollar contract with
Iran for offshore exploration at Sirri oil fields last
year. Originally, American Conoco company had the contract to
undertake the project but abandoned it because of a ban imposed
by Bill Clinton in June 1995.
</P>
<P>
Iranian oil industry has dismissed the sanction imposed by the
United States, saying it will be no short-term or long-term
impact on the oil and gas sector.
</P>
<P>
Velayati said that some companies of the United States had
attended an oil and gas conference held recently in Isfahan
defying Clinton's administrative order.
</P>
<P>
To thwart sanction by the United States, the Iranian oil
industry has announced a total of 11 key oil and gas projects
worth at least 7 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Iran had said that more than 120 foreign oil and gas companies
have offered their bids in the Iranian oil and gas sector.
</P>
<P>
Oil Minister Gholamreza Aghazadeh claimed that "having 92
billion barrels of crude oil reserves, the Islamic Republic of
Iran is one of the significant players in the world energy arena."
</P>
<P>
Iran is the second largest oil exporter in the world, which
pumps 3.6 million barrels of oil and exports 2.5 million barrels
of crude every day.
</P>
<P>
The oil industry is the pillar of Iran's economy. Iran earns
about 18 billion dollars by exporting crude oil each year and the
oil export revenue accounts for about 70 percent of the total
export of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
