<HEADLINE> Serious Drought Hitting Britain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 18 (Xinhua) -- The water industry's chiefs met here
today to discuss water supplies as Britain is plagued with the
worst drought in the past 200 years.
</P>
<P>
Water companies, regulators and environmental and consumer
lobby groups attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Reports said the government is angry at the huge amount of
water leakage from pipes -- estimated by some 3.64 billion litres
a day.
</P>
<P>
Water shortage has brought some areas close to cutting
essential domestic supplies and forced many consumers to endure
bans on watering their gardens.
</P>
<P>
The Water Services Association said the industry was trying to
encourage customers "to use water wisely, in the home, in the
garden and in the work place." 
</P>
</TEXT>
