<HEADLINE> Construction Begins on Henan's First Jointly-funded Power Plant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Construction began on the first
jointly-funded power plant in the city of Nanyang, central China's
Henan Province.
</P>
<P>
The Pushan Power Plant will have two 125,000-kw generation
units.
</P>
<P>
The power plant will be jointly funded with 1.43 billion yuan
(172 million US dollars) by AEP from the United States and two
local companies. It is expected to alleviate local power shortages
and improve the investment environment.  
