<HEADLINE> HK Air Cargo Records Double Digit Growth in April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 19 (Xinhua) -- The air cargo at Hong Kong's Kai
Tak International Airport rose 17.2 percent in April, Hong Kong
Air Cargo Terminals Limited (HACTL) announced here today.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, HK's single air cargo
terminal operator has processed over half a million tons of air
cargo, securing Kai Tak's position as the world's top
international cargo airport.
</P>
<P>
Among the total 139,861 tons handled last month, export cargo
increased by 18 percent over the same period last year to 64,691
tons, import cargo was up 14 percent to 57,985 tons, and
transshipment goods rose a remarkable 23.4 percent to 17,185 tons,
the HACTL listed.
</P>
<P>
Anthony Charter, managing director of the HACTL, said: "In
terms of a single air cargo complex, HACTL handles more tonnage
than any other operator in the world."
</P>
<P>
The rise in April "corroborates our estimates that the
long-term outlook for Hong Kong's air cargo is one of underlying
optimism and growth," he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
