<HEADLINE> China To Step Up Collection of Personal Earnings Tax </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 19 (Xinhua) -- China is expected to put more
efforts into the collection of individual earnings tax revenue,
which is expected to exceed the 20 billion yuan mark this year.
</P>
<P>
The government will take new measures to collect more personal
earnings tax this year, especially from people engaged in
architecture, performing arts, and advertising, according to an
official with the State Administration of Taxation.
</P>
<P>
It will also conduct a special examination nationwide to fight
against tax evasion more harshly, the official noted.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, a new law is to be drafted to regulate the collection
of the tax item, he said.
</P>
<P>
Since China first started to impose the tax item in 1980s, the
state revenue from the individual earnings has expanded from five
million yuan in 1981 to 19.3 billion yuan last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
