<HEADLINE> Some 280 Arrested for Violating Election Codes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Some 280 people were arrested
for violation of election codes in the capital city of
Tehran in the past few days, a security official said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Tosef-Reza Abulfathi, commander of the Law Enforcement Forces
in the Greater Tehran area, said that these people were
arrested because they tore off or destroyed posters or used
government facilities to promote their favorite candidates.
</P>
<P>
The competition is rather intense among two main rivals --
Parliament Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq-Nouri and former cultural and
Islamic guidance minister Mohammad Khatami as the countdown began
on the presidential elections slated for coming Friday.
</P>
<P>
The security official warned that any rally or march in
support of a candidate following their speeches is forbidden
without valid permits.
</P>
<P>
"Tearing off or destroying posters or placing one candidate's
poster on the other's is forbidden and those who are seen
doing in that way would be arrested and face law suit," he
warned.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Election Supervision Council of the Tehran
province today issued a statement asking the presidential
aspirants to be vigilant about the rules in their
campaign.
</P>
<P>
The council warned that the violators will face legal
charges punishable by imprisonment. It also announced three
telephone numbers for report of any violations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970519.0030 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stability of Rural Policies Stressed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, May 19 (Xinhua) -- The policies implemented in the
rural areas should be further stabilized, said a senior legislator
recently.
</P>
<P>
Tian Jiyun, vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the
Chinese National People's Congress (NPC), made this remark during
an inspection tour of northwest China's Gansu province from May 14
to 18.
</P>
<P>
He said that the rural productive forces should be further
enhanced, and the pace of getting rid of poverty should be
hastened.
</P>
<P>
According to Tian, the current policies implemented in the
rural areas include the household responsibility system, the
policy permitting some farmers to develop wealth, and the policy
to encourage the development of rural enterprises.
</P>
<P>
More technologies and agricultural machinery should be applied
so as to promote the rural productive forces and to help narrow
the development gap between the country's west and east regions,
he added.
</P>
<P>
"The central government will continue supporting the
development of the western region, while the government at all
levels in the west should emancipate their minds further from
traditional old ideas and introduce more funds from overseas and
seek more cooperative opportunities," Tian said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
