<HEADLINE> Afghan Northern Warlord Faces Rebellion: TV Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, May 19 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan northern warlord
Rashid Dostum was facing strong rebellion by one of his former
commander, Pakistani Television (PTV) reported today.
</P>
<P>
Dostum's former commander, Abdul Malik, is meeting with rebel
forces in the northwestern Faryab province of war-torn
Afghanistan, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Faryab province is reportedly under the control of Malik.
</P>
<P>
According to latest reports, PTV said, the rebel troops of
Malik were engaged with Dostum's forces in Mazar-e-Sharif,
Dostum's headquarters, about 300 kilometers northwest of Kabul.
</P>
<P>
The rebel forces have announced their support for the Afghan
Islamic militia Taliban, which controls more than two-thirds of
the Afghan territory, PTV said.  
