<HEADLINE> Moulinex to Invest Nine Million US dollars in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 19 (Xinhua) -- The French Moulinex Group, one of
the world's largest companies of small electrical home appliances,
has decided to invest over nine million US dollars in China.
</P>
<P>
The company will invest a total of 150 million yuan (18 million
US dollars) in Asia, more than half of which will be used in
China, the president of the Moulinex, Pierre Blayau, told a press
conference in Guangzhou today.
</P>
<P>
"China has a market with infinite potential," said Blayau,
who was among the entourage of French President Jacques Chirac to
visit Beijing and Shanghai, "our company should have come here
earlier."
</P>
<P>
Moulinex has just opened its first joint-venture in China,
Moulinex (China) Co. Ltd, in a small town of Zhongshan City in
south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
The joint-venture plans to produce 300,000 microwave ovens by
1998, using the patents from Moulinex. It will then produce other
small home appliances according to the demands of Chinese market.
</P>
<P>
Xiaolan Town, where the joint-venture is located, has a
population of 143,000 people, and turned over 4.56 billion yuan
(554 million US dollars) in industrial and agricultural output
value in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The output value of the French Moulinex, founded in 1932,
totaled eight billion Francs (about 1.4 billion US dollars) last
year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
