<TEXT>
<P>
Hong Kong, May 19 (Xinhua) -- The Provisional legislative
Council (PLC) of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
(HKSAR) today issued a statement inviting the public and
interested groups to express their views on its proposed societies
and public order bills.
</P>
<P>
The two bills, the Societies (Amendment) Bill 1997 and the
Public Order (Amendment) Bill 1997, were introduced by a senior
official of the HKSAR Chief Executive's Office to the PLC last
Saturday for the first and second readings.
</P>
