in Shenzhen Saturday, Michael Suen, secretary for policy
coordination of the HKSAR Chief Executive's Office, stressed that
the two amendment bills "aim at striking a proper balance between
civil liberties and social order" and "at guarding against
interference by foreign political forces in local political
activities."  
