<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, May 19 (Xinhua) -- The British Government launched a
campaign Monday against the tobacco firms to sponsor the sports
events.
</P>
<P>
British Health secretary Frank Dobson revealed that the
government's draft Bill to ban tobacco advertising would also
cover sponsorship.
</P>
<P>
Motor racing, cricket and snooker are the three sports likely
to be worst affected by the campaign.
</P>
<P>
