<HEADLINE> South Asian Trade Promotion Meeting Opens in Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 19 (Xinhua) -- The first regional meeting of the
trade promotion organizations of the South Asian Association for
Regional Cooperation (SAARC) member countries began here today.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meeting seeks to discuss the possibility of
networking of trade and investment related agencies in the region
as an added impetus to the ongoing efforts towards the development
of intra-regional trade within the member countries, according to
conference sources.
</P>
<P>
The sources said the meeting is represented by official
delegations at the highest level from trade promotion bureaus of
the SAARC countries.
</P>
<P>
SAARC groups Bangladesh, Bhutan, India, the Maldives, Pakistan,
Nepal and Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the meeting, Sri Lankan Minister of Internal and
External Trade, Commerce and Food K. Wickramaratna stressed the
need for in-depth studies on industries and products that could
give advantage to particular countries based on the strengths and
weaknesses in the region.
</P>
<P>
He said the respective countries can prepare lists of
industries and products that would be more competitive than the
other countries in the region.
</P>
<P>
He invited investors from the region to invest in those
industries.
</P>
<P>
The trade promotion organizations can prepare such lists in
consultation with their counterparts in other countries by way of
exchange of information.
</P>
<P>
He added this kind of networking would strengthen the trade
promotion organizations in the region and such cooperation will
lead to more meaningful action programs.  
</P>
