According to a spokesman for the Airport Authority, the two
licenses, which are amongst the world's biggest airport retail
concessions, have gone to the Swiss-HK joint venture Nuance-Watson
(HK) Limited.
</P>
<P>
The five-year-term perfumes and cosmetics licence gives the
joint venture the right to sell a comprehensive range of brands of
perfumes, cosmetics and toiletries within Hong Kong Sky Mall, the
world-class shopping mall within the passenger terminal at the new
 airport.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the airside general merchandise licence gives the
Nuance-Watson (HK) Limited the right to sell a wide selection of
merchandise within the Hong Kong Sky Mall.
</P>
<P>
Also today, the Airport Authority announced the award of the
licence for duty-free liquor and tobacco operations at the Hong
Kong Sky Mall.
</P>
<P>
The licence, the largest of its kind in the world, has been
awarded to Sky Connection Limited, a joint venture between two
major local conglomerates -- the Lai Sun Group and the New World
Group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
