<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Minister Confers with ROK Counterpart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier and Foreign
Minister Qian Qichen held talks here today with Yoo Chong-ha, his
counterpart from the Republic of Korea (ROK), exchanging views on
bilateral relations and other issues of mutual concern.
</P>
<P>
Extending a welcome to Yoo Chong-ha's China visit, Qian said
that China and ROK have witnessed comprehensive and rapid growth
in friendly cooperation in all fields since the two forged official
diplomatic ties, and the frequent exchanges of high-level visits
of between the two sides have enhanced mutual understanding and
trust.
</P>
<P>
The trade volume reached 20 billion US dollars from five
billion US dollars since official diplomatic relations were set
up. China has become the ROK's third largest trade nation while
the ROK is now China's fourth largest trade partner, Qian noted.
</P>
<P>
Qian went on to say that the two countries have reached an
extensive consensus on maintaining peace and stability in the
Korean Peninsula and on other major issues, the enhancement of
cooperation and coordination in international affairs contributes
greatly to the peace and stability in northeast Asia and Asia as a
whole.
</P>
<P>
Qian noted that China is satisfied with the status quo of
bilateral relations and results scored since the forging of
diplomatic ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Yoo Chong-ha said that the establishment of bilateral official
relations brings direct interests to the two countries and their
people, especially the exchanges of visits and mutual
understanding and trust between the leaders of the two countries
have greatly improved the continuous growth of friendly
cooperative relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Expressing satisfaction with the ROK over the rapid advancement
of cooperation in economy and trade between the two sides, Yoo
Chong-ha noted that the economies of the two countries are
complementary and have enjoyed wide potential, he believed that
the bilateral economic and trade cooperation will enter into a new
stage with the efforts.
</P>
<P>
They have reached consensus on the joint sponsorship of
commemorations of the fifth anniversary of establishment
of official diplomatic relations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
On the situation of the Korean Peninsula, Qian said, China
hopes for long-term peace and stability in the Korean Peninsula,
which is the basic principle in handling such issues.
</P>
<P>
To conduct dialogue and improve relations between the two sides
of the Korean Peninsula is significant to the relaxation of
tension in the Korean Peninsula and settling of the existing
problems, Qian said, adding that China endorses setting up
a peaceful mechanism for the Korean Peninsula and considers the
four-party negotiation of great significance to the relaxation
of situation on the peninsula and settlement of existing problems
concerning the peninsula, and that the four-party talks for
establishing a peaceful mechanism in the peninsula is both
pragmatic and feasible.
</P>
<P>
China hopes the parties concerned can reach agreement on
holding the four parties negotiation so as to promote the timely
establishment of the mechanism, Qian noted.
</P>
<P>
Furthermore, they also discussed the issue of Taiwan's outward
transport of nuclear waste. The guests were briefed on China's
position of principle on this issue.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan, and Chinese
Ambassador to ROK Zhang Tingyan, and ROK Ambassador ROK to China
Chong Wook Chung were among those present at the talks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
