<DOCNO> XIE19970519.0061 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Maintains Stable Prices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 19 (Xinhua) -- The price index of consumer goods
in China has fallen for 30 months running. How long it will last?
</P>
<P>
An official with the State Statistical Bureau said it will not
rebound sharply this year. The downward trend will continue as
long as the macro-economic control works.
</P>
<P>
In the first quarter of this year, the growth rate of consumer
goods has drifted to 5.2 percent. Economists predict that the
annual growth rate will not surpass six percent.
</P>
<P>
Macro-economic control played a decisive role in keeping the
price stable.
</P>
<P>
The strategic shift from seller's market to a buyer's market is
the internal factor of stable prices in China, said Ren Caifang,
head of the investigation team of the State Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
A buyer's market means an ample supply of commodities is on the
market with supply and demand balancing the price of the majority
of goods.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural development contributed greatly to sustained
stable prices. Consecutive good grain harvests have kept the farm
produce prices stable. The absolute price is declining.
</P>
<P>
Other leading factors included the readjustment of economic
structures and operation on a fairly large scale. Mass production
has reduced production cost and consequently led a drop in retail
price.
</P>
<P>
Chinese consumers are the beneficiaries of stable market. There
has been a buying spree for large-screen color television sets and
computers as a result of price cutting over the past year.
</P>
<P>
However, government officials and experts said, consumer
purchases were not as active as desired, which has restricted
production though it benefits the stability of prices.
</P>
<P>
This was partially caused by the laid-offs at enterprises in
China's transition of economic systems. Therefore, a key solution
to enliven the market is to create more job opportunities for the
jobless.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, housing and automobile have gradually become
the hot items for purchase in urban districts, which provide an
impetus for national economic development.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, rural areas have great potential. Higher income for
farmers will help stimulate the market, Ren said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970519.0062 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-19 </DATE_TIME>
