<HEADLINE> China to Hold Nationwide Inspection of Statistics Law </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 19 (Xinhua) -- The State Statistical Bureau, the
Ministry of Supervision, and the Bureau of Legislative Affairs
under the State Council will jointly conduct a nationwide
inspection this June, July, and August on the enforcement of the
Statistics Law.
</P>
<P>
Liu Hong, new director of the State Statistical Bureau,
released the information here today.
</P>
<P>
According to Liu, various localities and departments have
earnestly studied and carried out the Statistics Law since it was
revised last May, which has played an important role in improving
the accuracy of the statistics and quality of the statistical work.
</P>
<P>
The inspection will cover units at all levels and of all types
that organize the statistical surveys, including unofficial
organizations and overseas organizations and individuals, as well
as units and individuals who have obligations to provide
statistics.
</P>
<P>
Illegal behavior, such as making false reports and deceiving,
is an emphasis of the inspection.  
</P>
