<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Forum Highlights Law on Administrative Supervision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 19 (Xinhua) -- The law on Administrative
Supervision is of great significance to the improvement of China's
legal structure and system of administrative supervision, and
concrete measures must be taken to ensure its full implementation.
</P>
<P>
This is the opinion shared by senior Party and government
officials and legal experts attending today a Beijing forum on the
law's implementation.
</P>
<P>
The law was adopted by the Standing Committee of the Eighth
National People's Congress (NPC) on May 9, and came into force the
same day.
</P>
<P>
Buhe, vice-chairman of the NPC Standing Committee, told the
forum that it is necessary for all relevant departments and
personnel to work out concrete and feasible measures to safeguard
the integrity and authority of the law.
</P>
<P>
"People's congresses at all levels across the country should
also strengthen their supervision on the law's implementation, and
make every effort to correct immediately any activities in
violation of the law," he added.
</P>
<P>
State Councillor Li Guixian described the promulgation of the
law on administrative supervision as a major step China has taken
in the process of adopting a rule of law.
</P>
<P>
"The law will play a significant role in raising the
administrative efficiency, and will help improve the
decision-making capability and management skills of leading
officials at all levels," Li said.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, minister of supervision Cao Qingze demanded that
supervisory departments across the country take a serious attitude
towards studying, publicizing, and carrying out the law on
administrative supervision.
</P>
<P>
"Supervisory officials should seriously perform the duties the
law has entrusted them with, and exercise their power in strict
accordance with the law," said Cao, who is also vice-secretary of
the Central Commission for Discipline Inspection of the Communist
Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Today's forum was jointly hosted by the Ministry of
Supervision, the NPC Committee for Internal and Judicial Affairs,
the Commission of Legislative Affairs of the NPC Standing
Committee, and the Bureau of Legislative Affairs of the State
Council, China's cabinet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
