<HEADLINE> Li Peng Meets Hong Kong Delegation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng said here
today that after Hong Kong's return to the motherland, all
commercial activities conforming to the Basic Law will develop
smoothly and Chinese and foreign invested enterprises will enjoy
equal treatment.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with a delegation from the General Committee of the
Hong Kong General Chamber of Commerce led by its Chairman James P
C Tien, Li noted that there are 43 days remaining until Hong Kong
returns to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's return is a major historic event that will be
celebrated by people across China and also represents an important
step towards the reunification of the motherland, in accordance
with the great concept of "one country, two systems" put forward
by the late Deng Xiaoping.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that the implementation of "one country, two
systems" policy in Hong Kong and maintaining its long-term
prosperity and stability are not only the need of China, but also
of positive significance and far-reaching influence to
safeguarding peace and stability in the Asia-Pacific region and
the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that the Hong Kong General Chamber of
Commerce, as an influential industrial and commercial
organization, should contribute to Hong Kong's steady transition,
smooth transfer of the power, and its long-term development.
</P>
<P>
Li said that all people without prejudice will conclude that
the country will maintain the momentum of development.
</P>
<P>
Both Hong Kong and the inland areas are closely connected
economically. The inland's stability and development benefit Hong
Kong's prosperity and stability. Hong Kong's prosperity and
stability will be beneficial to the inland's development and
stability, and also to exchanges and cooperation between countries
and regions all over the world and China in economy, trade, and
technology.
</P>
<P>
Tien said the Hong Kong General Chamber of Commerce is a
commercial organization with a long history, which is broadly
representative and with global links.
</P>
<P>
Since 1979, he said, a great number of Hong Kong enterprises
have come to invest in the inland with the implementation of the
policy of reform and opening-up to the world.
</P>
<P>
Such development will keep on, he said, adding that all members
of the General Chamber of Commerce will contribute to maintaining
Hong Kong's prosperity and stability after its return to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
Wang Zhaoguo, head of the United Front Work Department of the
Chinese Communist Party Central Committee, attended the meeting.
</P>
</TEXT>
