<HEADLINE> Five Nigerian Robbers Beheaded in Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia today beheaded
five Nigerian nationals for robbing a bank, Saudi Interior
Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
In a statement carried by the official Saudi Press Agency,
the ministry said the five Nigerians, whose names were not
given, were publicly executed in the Red Sea coast-city of
Jeddah.
</P>
<P>
The agency said their heads were chopped off with a sword
after a court found them guilty of robbing a bank in the
city.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerians, carrying guns, entered the bank and locked
the bank's employees in a room, robbed the safety box and
escaped with a stolen car.
</P>
<P>
The statement also said an Afghan national was also
beheaded after being convicted of smuggling heroin inside his
body.
</P>
<P>
The execution raised to 38 the number of people put to
death in the Kingdom this year.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia enforces Islamic Sharia law by publicly
beheading convicted murderers, robbers, drug smugglers and
rapists. 
</P>
