slammed in another eight as Russia, 1993 world champion, scored an
easy win over China, making their first appearance in the world
championship.
</P>
<P>
Aleksandr Knezevic notched eight goals for Yugoslavia and
Dragan Skrbic added six to counter the nine goals from Lithuania's
Gediminas Bucys.
</P>
<P>
Redouane Saidi broke open a 6-3 game at halftime with five
goals as African champions Algeria defeated tournament newcomer
Saudi Arabia.
</P>
<P>
The preliminaries, being contested by 24 teams divided into
four groups, continue until next Sunday.
</P>
