<HEADLINE> 181 Tamil Rebels Killed In Northern Sri Lanka </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 19 (Xinhua) -- At least 181 rebels of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) have been killed during
the Operation "Jaya Skiuru" (Certain Victory) launched by
government troops last Tuesday in northern Sri Lanka, according to
military spokesman this evening.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the troops today continued to consolidate in
the recaptured areas of Nadunkerni and north of Omantai. Artillery
 fire was directed at rebel targets in the areas.
</P>
<P>
Rebel radio has so far confirmed their casualties as 181 killed
and 316 others injured. However, the rebels casualties are very
much higher than this, according to troops and other sources, the
spokesman pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Three leaders of the rebel women's cadre of the Wanni areas
have been killed in a face-to-face fight during the operation, he
said.
</P>
<P>
A total of eight soldiers had been killed and 29 injured in the
past day, he added.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a guerrilla war for a separate state
in the north and east of the country since 1983.  
</P>
