<HEADLINE> Jordan's Crown Prince Leaves for Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Jordan's Crown Prince Hassan left
here today on a 2-day working visit to Italy to further bilateral
rolations under the framework of a Euro-Jordanian partnership in
the domain of security, economy and culture, Radio Jordan
reported.
</P>
<P>
Hassan will first meet with Italian Prime Minister Romano Prodi
on bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
After this, the crown prince is expected to visit the Italian
Center for High Defense Studies and the NATO's College of Defense.
</P>
<P>
At the center, he will give a lecture on Jordan and the Middle
East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the center is expected to sign a memorandum of
cooperation with Jordan's Institute of Diplomacy.
</P>
<P>
Hassan is accompanied by Deputy Prime Minister for Development
Affairs and Prime Ministry Affairs Jawas Anani and Minister of
Foreign Affairs Fayez Tarawneh.
</P>
<P>
Jordan signed a culture agreement with Italy in January this
year.
</P>
<P>
Between 1992 and 1996, Italian exports to Jordan increased from
160 million U.S. dollars to more than 250 million dollars and the
Jordanian exports to Italy also increased by 5 times. Meanwhile,
Italy is the sixth largest source of official foreign bilateral
assistance to Jordan.
</P>
<P>
Jordan, now eager to establish a partnership with the European
Union and join the World Trade Organization, has intensified its
diplomacy in Europe.
</P>
<P>
At the beginning of this year, King Hussein and Hassan paid
separate visits to some European countries. 
</P>
