<HEADLINE> Lebanese Guerrilla Launches Suicide Attack on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, May 19 (Xinhua) -- A Lebanese Muslim guerrilla carried
out earlier this morning an apparent suicide attack on an Israeli
gunboat in the water opposite the south Lebanese port city of Sour
80 kilometers south of Beirut.
</P>
<P>
The pro-Syrian Amal Movement, which is headed by Lebanese
House Speaker Nabih Berri, claimed responsibility for the attack.
</P>
<P>
In a statement issued in Beirut, the moderate Shiite Muslim
organization said that one of its members launched around 5:00
a.m. (0200 GMT) an "operation of martyrdom targeting an Israeli
gunboat cruising in the water between Qleili to the north and the
Naqoura to the south."
</P>
<P>
The guerrilla "driving a small boat fully loaded with
explosives managed to approach the Israeli gunboat and blasted
himself, badly damaging the gunboat and killing and wounding all
the crew staff," the Amal statement added.
</P>
<P>
Radio Israel quoted an naval force spokesman as saying that
the Israeli maritime military foiled an attempt of bombing one of
its gunboats in the Mediterranean water some three kilometers
north of the Naqoura coast earlier this morning.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that the Israeli gunboat opened fire at a
small fishing boat loadful of explosives and driven by a Lebanese
resistance fighter, killing the militant and sinking the boat.
</P>
<P>
Sources in the U.N. Interim Force in Lebanon (UNIFIL), the
U.N. peacekeeping force operating in south Lebanon, said that an
Israeli gunboat fired machineguns at a Lebanese boat in the water
south of Qleili.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that the boat exploded in the gun fire, and
the only person aboard was killed.
</P>
<P>
Following the operation, Israeli forces imposed strict
blockade around the south Lebanese water and prevented any
Lebanese fishing boats from leaving their docks.
</P>
<P>
High tensions have shrouded south Lebanon, the last active
battlefront of the Arab-Israeli conflict, since the weekend,
after a series of clashes between Israeli occupation forces and
their client South Lebanese Army militia on the one side and
Lebanese guerrillas on the other.
</P>
<P>
Israeli warplanes also launched three air raids at suspected
guerrilla targets in south Lebanon and the Syrian-controlled
Western Beqaa in the last four days.
</P>
<P>
Nine Israeli soldiers were killed and more than 40 others
wounded in exchanges of fire with guerrillas in south Lebanon
since this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
