<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japan Trade Surplus More Than Doubled In April </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, MAY 19 (Xinhua) -- The weaker yen more than doubled
Japan's trade surplus in April from a year earlier, the Finance
Ministry announced on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Figures released on Monday showed that Japan's overall trade
surplus surged 163.7 percent, the highest growth rate since
January 1992.
</P>
<P>
The sensitive surplus with the United States shot up even more
strongly, rising 174.1 percent to 468.97 billion yen (4.1 billion
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The figures were not adjusted for seasonal factors.
</P>
<P>
Japan's trade surplus began growing in February for the first
time in 27 months and kept rising in March. 
</P>
</TEXT>
