<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets ROK Foreign Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, May 19 (Xinhua) -- China hopes its relations with the
Republic of Korea (ROK) will continue to develop, Chinese Premier
Li Peng told visiting ROK Foreign Minister Yoo Chong-ha here today.
</P>
<P>
Extending welcome to Yoo Chong-ha who is making his first visit
to China as ROK Foreign Minister, Li said that this year is the
fifth anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic ties between
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
"We are glad to see that since the diplomatic relations were
established, both countries have, continuously, stuck to all
principles set when we forged the ties, and developed friendly
cooperation in various fields on the basis of equality and mutual
benefit," Li said.
</P>
<P>
This has served to advance a healthy bilateral relationship
along a good-neighborly and cooperative track, Li added.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Yoo Chong-ha said bilateral relations have
scored remarkable progress in the past five years and the ROK
hopes to push the good-neighborly cooperative relations to a new
height in the wake of the fifth anniversary of the establishment
of the diplomatic ties.
</P>
<P>
He congratulated China as its government will soon resume the
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong and expressed thanks for
being invited to attend the forthcoming power handover ceremony in
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
On the Korean Peninsular situation, Li Peng said China, as a
close neighbor, is concerned about the developments and changes on
the peninsular and hopes that peace and stability will be
maintained there.
</P>
<P>
Li noted China has always held that the north and south of the
peninsular will solve their problems through dialogue and China is
willing to continue to play a constructive role in keeping peace
and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
Tang Jiaxuan, Chinese Vice-Foreign Minister, and Lu Congmin,
Deputy Director of the Foreign Affairs Office of the State
Council, were present at the meeting. 
</P>
</TEXT>
