<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yemen Urges Turkey to Observe Rules of Good </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANAA, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Yemen has called for Turkey's
compliance with rules of good neighborliness and to refrain from
military operations in Iraq, the Yemen News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
It quoted a Yemeni official source who asked not to be named as
saying that Yemen called on Turkey to resolve problems by
refraining from military escalation and direct coordination with
Iraq so that the interests of all the parties concerned can be
ensured.
</P>
<P>
Yemen was following with great concern the military activities
being carried out by Turkey in northern Iraq, the source said
Sunday evening.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish move threatened the Iraqi territorial integrity and
caused great harm to property and lives of the Iraqi people, added
the source.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted the source as saying that his country
reaffirms its rejection to the resort to force. And
Yemen hopes the Turkish government will end its military
activities in northern Iraq immediately, he said.
</P>
<P>
Turkish troops have entered northern Iraq since last Wednesday
to attack what Turkey called elements of Turkey's separatists of
the Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK). 
</P>
</TEXT>
