<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Badminton Championships Open in Glasgow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GLASGOW, Scotland, May 19 (Xinhua) -- The Fifth World Badminton
Mixed Team Championships for the Sudirman Cup opened in the
Scottish city of Glasgow on Monday.
</P>
<P>
A record of 59 countries and regions are competing in the
one-week long event which runs until May 24. The last championship
in Lausanne, Switzerland, held the previous record of 49.
</P>
<P>
Only six teams in the top Division A will vie for the Sudirman
Cup. Other countries and regions compete in the other seven
divisions.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion China, South Korea and England is in Group A
of the Division One, while 1995 world championship runner-up
Indonesia in Group B with Denmark and Sweden.
</P>
<P>
The top two teams in each of the groups sail into Friday's
semi-finals. The final is slated for Saturday.
</P>
<P>
There was no opening ceremony on Monday, where no Division One
teams has an outing. Few spectators appeared to watch, leaving the
stands at the Scotstoun Leisure Center almost empty.
</P>
<P>
In the first meeting completed in the championship, Lithuania
beat Chile 3-0 in Division 8.
</P>
<P>
The Sudirman Cup, named after later Indonesian Badminton
Association Vice President Sudirman, is an event between teams of
men and women shuttlers representing different countries and
regions.
</P>
<P>
Each clash between two teams consists of five matches, namely
the men's singles, women's singles, men's doubles, women's doubles
and mixed doubles, with the team taking three of them winning.
</P>
<P>
The 10th world individual championships, also staged here with
five individual titles at stake, follow the Sudirman Cup
competition and conclude on June 1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
