<HEADLINE> Japan's April Trade Surplus Surges 163.7 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Japan's merchandise trade surplus in
April increased 163.7 percent from a year earlier to 831.48
billion yen (7.2 billion U.S. dollars) amid strong exports of
automobiles and office supplies, the Finance Ministry said in a
preliminary report today.
</P>
<P>
The growth rate of the trade surplus is the highest since
January 1992, when it marked a 283.4 percent growth, the ministry
said. 
