<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kowloon-Beijing Through Train Inaugurated in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 19 (Xinhua) -- The Kowloon-Beijing Through Train
service formally commenced here today with the train from Beijing
arriving in Kowloon Station at 1:10 p.m. and departing for Beijing
at 3:00 p.m. today.
</P>
<P>
At a ceremony to inaugurate the first through train to
Beijing, K. Y. Yeung, chairman and chief executive of the
Kowloon-Canton Railway Corporation (KCRC), said that the through
train had drawn Beijing and Hong Kong closer.
</P>
<P>
He said he believes that the through train service between Hong
Kong and Beijing and Shanghai will promote Hong Kong's prosperity
and economic development in the coming years.
</P>
<P>
Donald Tsang, acting chief secretary, said that today we
celebrate the triumph of railway technology and the harvest of
five years of collaboration in railway operation between the
Chinese Ministry of Railways and the KCRC.
</P>
<P>
He said, interchanges between Hong Kong and the Chinese
mainland crate additional needs for railway services, adding that
the opening of the through train will strengthen ties between Hong
Kong with the interior areas.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Zhengqing, chief executive for the operation of railways
of the Chinese Ministry of Railways, said that the two through
trains from Beijing to Hong Kong and Shanghai to Hong Kong will
serve as bridges for the interchanges between the Chinese mainland
and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The service will promote Hong Kong's prosperity and stability,
he added.
</P>
<P>
The Kowloon-Beijing Through Train, consisting of 12 coaches to
accommodate 448 passengers, operates on alternative days. Running
through a distance of 2,500 kilometers, it calls at a number of
intermediate stations including Guangzhou East, Guangzhou,
Changsha, Wuchang and Zhengzhou. 
</P>
</TEXT>
