<HEADLINE> Five Belarussian Weightlifers Test Positive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Five Belarussian weightlifters have
tested positive for banned drugs, the country's Weightlifting
Federation sources said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The five were named as Andrei Marchenko, Vladimir Khlud, Alexei
Krushevich, Ruslan Doroshevich and Fyodor Mager. It was not
certain what substances had been found in their samples.
</P>
<P>
The samples taken from the five would be subjected to further
tests and the weightlifters could face sanctions or fines.
</P>
<P>
The incident cast a dark cloud to the Belarussian squad's
participation in the European Championships slated for this week
in Croatia.
</P>
<P>
Marchenko represents Belarus in the 76 kilogram class, Khlud in
91 kg, Mager at 108 kg and Krushevich and Doroshevich both lift in
the over 108 kg division. 
</P>
</TEXT>
