<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cyclonic Storm Likely to Hit Bangladesh Coast Tonight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Dhaka, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Latest Radar observation indicates
that a severe cyclonic storm with a core of hurricane wind is
moving northeastwards and may cross Bangladesh's southern coast
area by this evening, Storm Warning Center in a bulletin said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Maximum sustained wind within 74 kilometers of the hurricane
center is about 180 kilometers per hour (kph) rising to 200 kph or
more, said the bulletin.
</P>
<P>
Maritime ports of southern Chittagong and Cox's Bazar have been
advised to keep hoisted great danger signal Number ten.
</P>
<P>
Under the influence of the hurricane, moderately heavy
rainfalls are likely to occur over the coastal districts and low
lying areas of these districts are likely to be inundated by storm
surge.
</P>
<P>
All fishing boats and trawlers over north Bay of Bengal have
been advised to remain in shelter till further notice, the
bulletin added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, a round the clock control room has been set up in
the Home Ministry for proper supervision of the tasks of the
Ministry and departments under it in tackling the post-cyclone
situation in the affected areas.
</P>
<P>
A deputy secretary of the Home Ministry has been appointed as
liaison officer to maintain liaison with the control room of the
Ministry of Disaster Management and Relief.
</P>
<P>
Besides, members of police, Coast Guard and Civil Defense have
been instructed to extend all sorts of cooperation and assistance
to the local bodies in facing the cyclone.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
