<DOCNO> XIE19970519.0113 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka Launches Safe Drinking Water Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka recently launched a water
supply project with the aim of providing safe drinking water to
rural areas by the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
The National Water Supply and Drainage Board (NWSDB) of Sri
Lanka has already commenced construction of 7,500 tube wells and
will help construct 1,000 deep wells per year in the rural areas,
the NWSDB sources said.
</P>
<P>
They noted that this program is being implemented with the
participation of the rural community and the main objective of
this project is to make them aware of their responsibilities in
maintaining the wells.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that this rural water supply scheme was
inaugurated by the NWSDB in response to a decision taken by the
United Nation's International Drinking Water Supply Program.
</P>
</TEXT>
