<HEADLINE> Asia Oil, Gas Conference to Be Held in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, May 19 (Xinhua) -- The second Asia Oil and Gas
Conference and Exhibition (AOGC) 1997 will be held here on June
9-10.
</P>
<P>
The two-day conference with the theme "Asia: Preparing for the
Next Millennium" organized by the Asian Strategy and Leadership
Institute (ASLI) and Conference Connecting Inc. will be officiated
by Malaysia's Acting Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim who will present
the keynote address, ASLI president Mirzan Mahathir announced here
today at a news conference.
</P>
<P>
According to the ASLI chief, some 30 foreign and local experts
in the oil and gas industry will present 16 topics addressing
future trends, strategic issues and challenges facing the
petroleum industry in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
The annual event, a major one in the region, will bring
together key players in the oil and gas industry to deliberate on
issues concerning the economy, governmental regulations, the
deregulation process, supply availability and future direction of
the petroleum industry.
</P>
<P>
"AOGC '97 will be the premier forum for companies to interact,
discuss common issues and areas for mutual cooperation and forge
new strategic alliances," he said.
</P>
<P>
The response from participants is tremendous, he said, adding
that more than 400 industry players from all over the world have
registered for the event and like at last year's AOGC, most who
have registered are from Europe.
</P>
<P>
To ensure high-quality and success of the event, Mirzan said
the organizers have appointed a distinguished six-member advisory
panel and a prominent eight-member management council.  
</P>
