<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Weaker As Markets Await US Rate News </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, May 19 (Xinhua) -- The Australian dollar price closed
weaker as the market waited for news on whether the U.S. Federal
Reserve will lift its official interest rates.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed today at 77.49 US cents down from
77.61 US cents on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Federal Open Market Committee (FOMC) meets on Tuesday night
in the U.S. and most market participants believe there is a 50
percent chance that it will lift rates.
</P>
<P>
At its last meeting in March the Federal Reserve raised the
funds target rate for the first time in two years, to 5.50 percent
from 5.25 percent.
</P>
<P>
Macquarie Bank foreign exchange dealer Scott Hill said he
expected a weakening of the value of the Australian dollar if
rates in the U.S. are lifted.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar closed at 89.94 Japanese yen, down from
90.54 yen on Friday and at 1.3118 German marks from 1.3219 marks.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
