<HEADLINE> South Korea Takes Last Title in Pusan East Asian Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PUSAN, May 19 (Xinhua) -- South Korea was defeated by Japan 1-0 in
the last soccer game but still won the last gold medal from the soccer
round-robin tournament at the second East Asian Games here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Terada Shuhei headed in the lone goal with eight minutes into the
second half, helping Japan secure the silver medal in the six-team
tournament.
</P>
<P>
The host won the top honour with four straight wins before the
day's defeat for 12 points.
</P>
<P>
Japan edged China with goal differential as both squads finished 10
points from three wins, one draw and one loss. Japan outscored China
with 20-4 against 15-7 as the latter took the bronze medals.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan finished fourth with two wins, two draws and one defeat.
</P>
<P>
In the last action at the second East Asian Games, the host missed
its chances when Woo Yung-moon kicked his freekick to the bar before
two shots at the goal-mouth melee with five minutes to go were blocked
by the Japanese goalie and its defender.
</P>
<P>
In other actions of the day, China played a scoreless game with
Kazakhstan while Mongolia outscored Guam 4-0 to record its first
victory in five outing in the tournament.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia finished fifth with one win against four losses while Guam
was kept in the cellar with five straight losses.
</P>
<P>
Guam scored one goal but suffered 57 ones in its five games at the
six-team tournament, including a 1-20 defeat against Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
