<HEADLINE> Philippine President Meets WTO Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
assured the World Trade Organization (WTO) today of his country's
support for opening up the finance and information technology
sectors in the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
Ramos made the assurance in a meeting with WTO Director General
Renato Ruggiero, which was held on the sidelines of the 30th
International General Meeting of the Pacific Basin Economic
Council (PBEC).
</P>
<P>
Ramos told Ruggiero the Philippines had consistently supported
agreements on information technology during the Asia Pacific
Economic Cooperation meeting in Manila last November.
</P>
<P>
Ramos also outlined initiatives undertaken by the Philippines
in promoting free and open trade in the region, environmental
preservation, technology transfer, human resources protection,
telecommunications and infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
Ruggiero said he was impressed by the economic growth of the
Philippines over the past five years, its rising exports and
improved record on debt services.
</P>
<P>
Ruggiero is here to attend the three-day annual PBEC meeting,
which opened today to discuss the changing business environment in
the Asia-Pacific region.
</P>
<P>
Ruggiero will deliver a speech on the progress of the WTO
Tuesday at the meeting, according to the agenda.  
</P>
