<HEADLINE> 1997 China Panda Gold Coin to Be Issued in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 19 (Xinhua) -- 1997 China Panda Gold Coin,
issued by the People's Bank of China and minted by the Shanghai
and Shenyang Mints, will be publicly offered both in Hong Kong and
Macao from May 20, a spokesman of China Great Wall Coins
Investments Ltd. said here today.
</P>
<P>
Minted with unique technology and distributed by banking
offices of Bank of China Group in Hong Kong, the coin features the
panda's hair, and fully displays the lovely character of giant
panda, the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The obverse side of the coin bears the Prayer Hall in the
Temple of Heaven in Beijing, a classic work of Chinese
architecture, and the reverse side is the unique image of giant
panda, he said.
</P>
<P>
Its face value of the coin is 100 yuan, 50 yuan, 25 yuan, 10
yuan, and 5 yuan respectively and it has specifications: 1 oz, 1/2
oz, 1/4 oz, 1/10 oz and 1/20 oz.  
</P>
