<DATE_TIME> 1997-05-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Machinery, Electronics Exports Increasing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Exports of machinery and
electronics products from China have seen a steady rise in the
past several years, with electronic information products heading
the list.
</P>
<P>
Machinery and electronics products have been China's No. 1
export commodities for two consecutive years, and have accounted
for 31.9 percent of the country's total exports.
</P>
<P>
China's total machinery and electronics exports stood at 48.2
billion US dollars in 1996, up 10 percent from 1995.
</P>
<P>
Hi-tech products including program-controlled exchanges,
optical fibre telecommunications equipment, and computers and
software are making up an increasingly larger portion of machinery
and electronics exports, according to officials with the Ministry
of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
