<HEADLINE> Fuzhou to Attract Overseas Funds to Develop Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Fuzhou, capital of southeast China's
Fujian Province has listed 130 agricultural projects to attract
overseas investment this year.
</P>
<P>
The projects involve infrastructure construction, planting,
tourism, farm products processing, and township enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The city signed 64 overseas-funded agricultural projects last
year, with contracted investment reaching 120 million US
dollars, of which 30 has been approved with an investment of 44
million US dollars in real terms. So far, the total
overseas-funded projects have reached 250 involving more than 240
million US dollars in overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
The city intends to upgrade the management of its traditional
agriculture through introduction of overseas funds, technologies
and advanced equipment.
</P>
<P>
Fuzhou has now set up 10 bases to export local agricultural
products and is running more than 1,000 export-oriented township
enterprises. 
</P>
