<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Second PLA Advance Party Arrives in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, May 19 (Xinhua) -- The second advance team of the
Chinese People's Liberation Army (PLA) Garrison in the future Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region came to Hong Kong this
afternoon, to join the first advance party here.
</P>
<P>
A total of 66 PLA men, riding 14 military vehicles including
jeeps, coaches, transportation and communications vehicles, went
through Hong Kong's Lok Ma Chau Border Control Point at about
13:00.
</P>
<P>
The second team consisting of 18 field officers, 23 company
officers, two administrative staff and 23
soldiers, is expected to split into four groups to be stationed
in the Prince of Wales Barracks, Gun Club Hill Barracks, Sek Kong
Camp and Stonecutters Island Barracks.
</P>
<P>
A third party of 90 will arrive on May 30, to be stationed in
the Prince of Wales Barracks, Stanley Fort, Callipoli Lines,
Cassino Lines, Osborn Barracks and Boham Towers.
</P>
<P>
The first advance party of 40 led by Major General Zhou Borong,
deputy commander of the future PLA HKSAR Garrison, came
here on April 21. They are stationed in the Prince of Wales
Barracks
and Stonecutters Island Barracks.
</P>
<P>
All together, there will be 196 advance PLA personnel stationed
in Hong Kong. These PLA soldiers, all unarmed, are in Hong Kong
to make practical preparations for the future PLA garrison to take
over the responsibility for the defense of Hong Kong, including
familiarization with the military sites and coordination of
communications support and movement of supplies.
</P>
<P>
The formation of the PLA garrison to be stationed in Hong Kong
was completed on January 28, 1996. Made up of PLA ground, naval
and
air forces, and with strict political, military and disciplinary
training, the garrison will be officially stationed in Hong Kong
at zero hour on July 1, when Hong Kong will return to the embrace
of its motherland -- China.
</P>
<P>
The military forces have been formed in accordance with the PLA
missions stipulated in China's Constitution and the relevant
stipulation of the Basic Law that the central government shall be
responsible for the defense of the Hong Kong Special
Administration
Region, to safeguard state sovereignty, reunification and
territorial
integrity and maintain the prosperity and stability in the region.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
