<HEADLINE> Sautin Wins 10m Platform at Mexican Diving Tourney </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champion Dimitri Sautin
of Russia captured the title of the 10-meter platform on the final
day of the Mexican diving international tournament in Juarez on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Sautin, winner of the event in the Atlanta Olympics, scored 95
points in his last dive for a total of 715, beating the tourney
record of 710 set by American legend Greg Louganis in 1984.
</P>
<P>
American Brian Gillooly finished second with 557 and German
Heiko Meyer totalled 555 for the third.
</P>
<P>
Russia won four golds out of six on offer during the four-day
competition, with the other two going to the United States.
