<HEADLINE> Taiwan Increases Investment in Neighboring Fujian Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Taiwan has invested 850 million US
dollars in real terms in Zhangzhou city in its neighboring Fujian
province, forming the largest source of investment to the city.
</P>
<P>
The total investment coming through Taiwan almost equals to the
combined amount of investment from foreign countries or regions.
</P>
<P>
During the first three months of this year, the city approved
the establishment of 69 new Taiwanese-funded enterprises with a
total contracted investment of 168 million US dollars. The local
Taiwanese-funded enterprises earned nearly 100 million US dollars
in foreign exchange from exports during January and March.
</P>
<P>
So far, the city has ratified 847 Taiwan-funded enterprises,
with contracted Taiwanese investment exceeding three billion US
dollars. More than 500 of the enterprises have gone into operation
and account for one-third of output value generated by the
outside-funded businesses.
</P>
<P>
Of all the Taiwan-funded enterprises, 308 are involved in
agriculture, ranging from planting, aquatics to processing and
packaging. 
</P>
