<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Voter Registration Starts today in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Voter registration for the coming
general election in Kenya starts this morning and is expected to
register more than ten million voters.
</P>
<P>
According to the Electoral Commission of Kenya (ECK), some
40,000 clerks have been employed for 12,500 voter registration
centers all over the country.
</P>
<P>
Each of the 210 constituencies in the east African country has
an average of six registration officers and assistants who will
be in charge of the clerks.
</P>
<P>
The voter registration exercise will last for 35 days until
June 22.
</P>
<P>
More registration centers have been established countrywide in
an effort to reduce the time applicants will spend at the center,
According to ECK Chairman Zacchaeus Chesoni.
</P>
<P>
The ECK chairman last week announced that both the old and new
ID cards would be accepted during the exercise as some people
feared that those who had not received the new generation of ID
cards would be locked out of the exercise. 
</P>
</TEXT>
