<HEADLINE> Guangdong's Economy to Grow 11 Percent This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, May 19 (Xinhua) - The economy of South China's
Guangdong province will continue to grow at last year's pace -11
percent- for the current year, with its industry registering a
growth rate of 15 percent.
</P>
<P>
This is part of the latest research results sponsored by the
provincial government and is compiled into the province's annual
"blue book."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the province's urban and rural resident's per capita
income is estimated to be 71 percent and 65 percent higer
respectively than the national average this year, said the "blue
book."
</P>
<P>
Guangdong province achieved a GDP of 609.5 billion yuan last
year, which was 11 percent higher than the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The GDP figure is 8.5 times that of 1980, when the province
opened itself to the outside world and initiated reform.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the province's retail price index rose 4.4 percent,
which was 1.7 percentage points less than the national average.
</P>
</TEXT>
