<HEADLINE> Iran Happy with Self-Styled Zairean Head of State </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, May 19 (Xinhua) -- Iran said here today that it is
delight with the transfer of Zaire's power to Laurent Kabila, who
proclaimed himself head of state and renamed the country as
Democratic Republic of Congo Sunday.
</P>
<P>
But Foreign Ministry Spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi did not
mention whether Iran officially recognizes the Kabila government
or not.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman expressed hope that Kabila's taking power in
that country might end the hardships of its people.
</P>
<P>
He noted that as a rule, the Islamic republic of Iran respects
the will of other nations.
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that Kabila would bring peace and stability
to the country and fulfill the expectations of the people in Zaire.
</P>
<P>
President Mobutu left Kinshasa, capital of Zaire, Friday after
Kabila's troops approached the capital.
</P>
<P>
Zairean government spokesman Kin-Kiey Mulumba announced the
same day that the president would not "take any part in the
government" of the country, adding the Zairean law permits Mobutu
to effectively step aside without actually resigning as
president. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
