<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Produces More Fiber-Optic Cable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WUHAN, May 19 (XINHUA) -- China has seen a fast growth in its
production of fiber-optic products and optical cable over the past
decade following a wide application and popularity of fiber-optic
telecommunications technology in the country.
</P>
<P>
The country made 600,000 km of fiber-optic products in 1996, meeting
only 60 percent its domestic market demands, and produced 400,000
km of optical cable in the same year, fully meeting domestic
market demands.
</P>
<P>
It has also exported 400,000 km of fiber-optic products since
1992 when Changfei Fiber-Optic, Optical Cable Co. Ltd based in
Wuhan, capital of central China's Hubei Province, and the United
States signed China's first contract for overseas marketing of
fiber-optic products.
</P>
<P>
Changfei Company is China's biggest professional fiber-optic
and optical cable manufacturer. It is jointly funded by the
Ministry of Posts and Telecommunications, Wuhan City Government,
and the Philips Company of the Netherlands at a cost of 500 million
yuan in 1988, with the Chinese side controlling 62.5 percent of the
stake. 
</P>
</TEXT>
