<HEADLINE> South China Region Develops Priority Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, May 19 (Xinhua) -- South China's Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Region earned more than 12.7 billion yuan in industrial
added value during the first quarter this year, up 7.1 percent
over the same period of 1996.
</P>
<P>
The region has made efforts to develop its leading
profit-making industries, which cover the areas of sugar
cane-pressing, non-ferrous metals, machinery, automobiles, and
building materials.
</P>
<P>
The region now leads the country in its sugar industry. And, it
also intends to have an annual production capacity of 150,000
minivans by the turn of the century. It will also give priority
to cement plants to build up the local businesses in construction
materials.
</P>
<P>
The region will also apply technological know-how to its
leading and high-tech industries and enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The number of enterprises in the region with an annual
industrial output value exceeding 100 million yuan has reached 70,
which contribute nearly 70 percent of the local total profits
from industrial businesses. 
</P>
