<HEADLINE> Yeltsin to Attend Signing Ceremony of Russia-NATO Act </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin will
go to Paris on May 26 to attend the signing ceremony of the
Russia-NATO Founding Act, said French President Jacques Chirac
here today.
</P>
<P>
Chirac made the announcement at the airport before he left for
home. The Russia-NATO accord is scheduled to be signed in Paris on
May 27.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the accord, Chirac said, "This is Russia's victory
and a personal victory for President Yeltsin."
</P>
<P>
Chirac made a brief stopover in Moscow on his way back from an
official visit to China and met with his Russian counterpart.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, said a Kremlin statement, was held "in a spirit of
openness and mutual understanding," with a focus on bilateral ties
and current world issues, including the document on Russia-NATO
ties.
</P>
<P>
The French head of state will host the signing ceremony to
demonstrate France's role in European Security reforms. 
</P>
