<HEADLINE> Pharmaceutical Joint Venture Set Up in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, May 19 (Xinhua) -- A Sino-Japanese joint-venture has
been established at the Shanghai Bio-pharmaceutical Science and
Technology Industrial Center.
</P>
<P>
The Kirin Kunpeng Bio-Pharmaceutical Co. Ltd., with a total
investment of about 30 million US dollars, is a joint-venture of
the Shanghai Kunpeng Investment and Development Co. Ltd. and
Japanese Kirin Brewery Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The project is the first of its kind at the center, which is
jointly sponsored by the State Science and Technology Commission,
the Ministry of Public Health, the State Pharmaceutical
Administration, and the Shanghai city government.
</P>
<P>
The center is located in Zhangjiang Hi-tech Park in Pudong
New Development Area of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Ten more bio-pharmaceutical projects will be built at the
center, with a total investment of more than 800 million yuan (96
million US dollars) this year.
</P>
<P>
The sales volume of the center is estimated at ten billion yuan
(1.2 billion US dollars) by the year 2000, or more than one-third
of the city's total sales volume of bio-pharmaceutical products.
</P>
</TEXT>
