<HEADLINE> U.N. Chief Visits Austria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, May 18 (Xinhua) -- United Nations Secretary-General
Kofi Annan arrived in Vienna Sunday on a four-day official visit.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Annan will inspect some U.N. agencies in the
city, such as the U.N. Office, the International Atomic Energy
Agency and the U.N. Industrial Development Organization.
</P>
<P>
The Austrian government, which attached great importance to
the visit, was worried about the status of Vienna as a U.N. city
after the U.N. reforms, newspaper reports said.
</P>
<P>
However, after meeting with Annan, Austrian Foreign Ministry
State Secretary Benita Ferrero-Waldner said that the city would
keep its current status.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. chief will also meet with Austrian President Thomas
Klestil, Chancellor Viktor Klima and other Austrian officials.
</P>
