<HEADLINE> ATP to Change Ranking System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Tennis ranking system could be changed
after seven years' operation in hopes to encourage players to do
their best at the Grand Slams and other major tournaments, local
reports said here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Under the current system, players' rankings are calculated on
the results of their best 14 tournaments, allowing the worst to
be dropped.
</P>
<P>
But ATP is considering basing them on performances at the four
Grand Slam tournaments plus the current Super Nine series, which
could be reduced to eight or even seven. Every performance would
count.
</P>
<P>
Players who failed to appear at these would get a zero in
the rankings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
