<HEADLINE> Donovan Bailey Wins 100m in Vancouver </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Canadian 100m Olympic champion
Donovan Bailey scored an easy win in the same event at an
international meeting in Vancouver on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Bailey, running in Canada for the first time since last June,
clocked 9.99 seconds for the win, 0.15 second off his world record
set in the Atlanta Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
So far this season, Bailey has run just one 100m race in Rio
De Janeiro three weeks ago. He won there with a time of 10.13
seconds.
</P>
<P>
Most observers regarded Sunday's race as a warm-up by Bailey
prior to his June 1 race over 150m in Toronto against American
Michael Johnson who won the Olympic gold both in the 200m and 400.
</P>
