<HEADLINE> Latvia Beats Estonia in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Latvia rallied from one goal down at
halftime to beat Estonia 3-1 in their World Cup European group
four qualifying match in Tallinn on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Indrek Zelinski opened the account for Estonia only one minute
after the kick-off.
</P>
<P>
But Vladimir Babitches levelled the score in the 53rd minute,
Aleksandr Jeliseev put Latvia ahead 2-1 in the 78th.
</P>
<P>
Latvia went down 3-1 finally when Marek Lemsalu scored an own
goal four minutes before the final whistle.
</P>
<P>
Group standings (tabulated under games played, won, drew, lost,
goals for, against and points):
</P>
<P>
