<HEADLINE> Exiled Mobutu Arrives at Togo's Capital of Lome </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRAZZAVILLE, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Exiled former Zairean
president Mobutu Sese Seko today arrived at Lome, Togo, according
to Zaire's state television report tonight.
</P>
<P>
But it is still not sure whether Lome is the final destination
of Mobutu's exile trip.
</P>
<P>
Togolese President Gnassingbe Eyadema has been widely regarded
as a great friend of Mobutu.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, unconfirmed reports said Mobutu, driven away by the
Alliance of the Democratic Forces for the Liberation of
Congo-Zaire led by Laurent Kabila, had paid a one-day tour of
Morocco before heading for an European country for exile.
</P>
<P>
Kabila on Saturday declared himself head of state of Zaire,
and changed name of the country to the Democratic Republic of
Congo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
