<HEADLINE> Exiled Mobutu in Lome for Transit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRAZZAVILLE, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Togo's official television
confirmed tonight that Zaire's exiled president Mobutu Sese Seko
today arrived at Lome, Togo, before heading for Morocco.
</P>
<P>
Lome is merely a transit stop for cancer-torn Mobutu, the TV
report, monitored here quoted a Togolese government spokesman as
saying.
</P>
<P>
But it is still not sure whether Morocco is the final
destination of Mobutu's exile trip.
</P>
<P>
The report added that Mobutu would discuss with President
Gnassingbe Eyadema over the situation in Zaire and his own
personal future.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said Mobutu, driven away by the Alliance of
the Democratic Forces for the Liberation of Congo-Zaire led by
Laurent Kabila, would make a short visit of Morocco before
heading for an European country for exile.
</P>
<P>
Kabila on Saturday declared himself head of state of Zaire,
and changed name of the country to the Democratic Republic of
Congo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
