<HEADLINE> World Museums Day Celebrated in Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, May 18 (Xinhua) -- The World Museums Day was celebrated
today in Greece with the free entry to all of the country's
museums.
</P>
<P>
Speaking on the occasion of World Museums Day in the northern
city of Thessaloniki today, Greek Culture Minister Evangelos
Venizelos said "museums are the most modern form of culture. It is
the sector which vindicates our cultural heritage in the
consciousness of Greeks and foreigners alike."
</P>
<P>
The ministry has announced a pilot program for the upgrading of
services offered in 12 of the country's largest museums.
</P>
<P>
The program involves making museums more vital and
visitor-friendly through the introduction of various services
beyond the dry exhibition of artifacts.
</P>
<P>
The theme of this year's celebration is "the struggle against
the illegal trade of our cultural heritage". 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
