<HEADLINE> Kenya to Recognize New Government in Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi
today announced that the Kenyan government will recognize the
government to be formed by Laurent Kabila in Zaire, the Kenya
News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Moi made the remarks at a public rally in Kirinyaga District
of Central Province.
</P>
<P>
He noted that following a telephone conversation, he is
satisfied that Kabila has good intentions for the people of
Zaire.
</P>
<P>
The president stressed that all along Kenya's position has
been to champion peace and the respect of sanctity of human life.
</P>
<P>
Moi said that his crusade in striving to bring about
peace in the central African region is because of his beliefs
that human life is precious and bloodshed must be avoided at all
costs.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Kenyan Foreign Minister Kalonzo Musyoka said this morning
that Kenya is willing to work with the new government in Zaire.
</P>
<P>
The minister noted that Kenya has maintained a "positive
neutrality" over the situation in Zaire all along but it
supported the people of the country.
</P>
<P>
Laurent Kabila yesterday proclaimed himself Head of State of
Zaire and renamed the country as the Democratic Republic
of Congo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
