<HEADLINE> Finnish President Winds up Visit to Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Finnish President Martti
Ahtisaari left here for home today after winding up a three-day
state visit in Tanzania during which he held official talks with
President Benjamin Mkapa.
</P>
<P>
To see him off at the Dar es Salaam International Airport were
Tanzanian President Mkapa, Vice-President Omar Ali Juma, Prime
Minister Frederick Sumaye and Zanzibar President Salmin Amour.
</P>
<P>
According to the State House sources, during talks with Mkapa,
Ahtisaari assured Tanzania of continued assistance
in the economic, infrastructure, forestry and social amenities
fields.
</P>
<P>
The two presidents exchange ideas on the situation in the
Great Lakes Region, including the magnitude of the refugee burden
on Tanzania and security problems in Burundi and Zaire.
</P>
<P>
They also expressed the hope to enhance co-operation in the
international fora, especially at the United Nations to ensure
an equal distribution of available world resources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
