<HEADLINE> IGAD Summit to Be Held to Solve Sudan Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, May 18 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi
today announced that an Inter-governmental Authority on
Development (IGAD ) summit will soon be held to solve the crisis
in southern Sudan, according to a Kenya News Agency report today.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan leader was speaking at a public rally in Kirinyaga
District, Central Province.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, peace talks were held in Kenya between
Ugandan President Yoweri Museveni and Sudanese President Hassan
el Bashir to iron out their long-standing differences.
</P>
<P>
In a communique issued after the peace talks, the two
presidents requested President Moi, current IGAD chairman, to
convene an IGAD summit to pursue the course of peace in southern
Sudan and in the region.
</P>
<P>
The Kenyan head of state who facilitated the peace talks
commended the two leaders for their courage and commitment to
peace and stability in the IGAD region.
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that diplomatic activities will be
embarked upon to promote this peace initiative among all IGAD
member states. 
</P>
</TEXT>
